  "Metadata" -> {
   "built" -> "{2026, 4, 12, 17, 57, 48.420016}", 
    "history" -> {"12", "", "", ""}, "context" -> "QuantumMob`Q3`", 
    "keywords" -> {
     "quantum entanglement", "Schmidt decomposition", 
      "Singular value decomposition"}, "specialkeywords" -> {}, 
    "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True, "label" -> 
    "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> "QuantumMob/Q3",
     "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "SchmidtDecomposition[v, {d1, d2}] returns the Schmidt decomposition of \
the vector v in a tensor-product space of two vector spaces of dimensions d1 \
and d2. SchmidtDecomposition[v, {d1, d2, ...}, {i1, i2, ...}, {j1, j2, ...}] \
returns the Schmidt decomposition of the vector v in a tensor-product space \
of multiple vector spaces of dimensions d1, d2, ..., where the i1th, i2th, \
... spaces are grouped into one part and the j1th, j2th, ... spaces are \
grouped into the other part. SchmidtDecomposition[expr, {i1, i2, ...}, {j1, \
j2, ...}] returns the Schmidt decomposition of the state vector expr, where \
the i1th, i2th, ... qubits are grouped into one part and the j1th, j2th, ... \
qubits are grouped into the other part. SchmidtDecomposition[expr, {a1, a2, \
...}, {b1, b2, ...}] returns the Schmidt decomposition of the state vector \
expr, where the qubits a1, a2, ... form one part and the qubits b1, b2, ... \
form the other part of the bipartite system.", "synonyms" -> {}, 
    "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> "SchmidtDecomposition", "titlemodifier" -> 
    "", "metadescription" -> "", "windowtitle" -> "SchmidtDecomposition", 
    "type" -> "Symbol", "uri" -> "QuantumMob/Q3/ref/SchmidtDecomposition"}},
